Package app.viewmanagers

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    HelpViewManager
    View manager for the Help View.
    InputFieldViewManager
    View Manager for the inputField.
    RootViewManager
    This is the root view manager of all view managers/components.
    SettingsViewManager
    This is the view manager for the Settings component, which appears as a pop up when "settings" is entered as a command or if the settings button is clicked.
    SidebarViewManager
    This class manages the Sidebar control, which consists of various buttons for interacting with the application.
    TaskListCellViewManager
    Each TaskListCell represents a single TodoItem.
    TaskListViewManager
    TaskListViewManager manages the ListView object, which is responsible for creating and displaying individual ListCell objects that represent a TodoItem each.
    TitleBarViewManager
    The TitleBar contains a label that shows the user their current context, as well as a drop-down choice box that lets the user switch how the tasks are sorted by.

    Enum Description
